{"parse":{"title":"how are you","pageid":35900,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{phrasebook|en|Greetings}}\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|en|how're you||informal}}\n* {{alt|en|HRU||initialism}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/haʊ ˈɑː juː/|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/haʊ ˈɑɹ ju/|a=GA}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-how_are_you.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/hæɔ ˈaː jʉː/|/hæɔ ˈaː jə/|a=AU}}\n** {{audio|en|en-au-how_are_you.ogg|a=AU}}\n\n===Phrase===\n{{en-head|phr|head=?}}\n\n# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} An informal greeting, not requiring a literal response. In form a question, and thus followed by a question mark. Typical responses include:\n#: {{ux|en|I'm very well, thank you. '''How are you'''? ''(formal)''<br>[[I'm fine, thank you]]. ''/'' <br> Fine, thanks. ''(informal) /'' <br> Fine, and you? ''(informal)''}}\n# {{lb|en|idiomatic|Ireland}} (Following a noun phrase; stress on ''are'') An expression of derision, that the preceding referent is unworthy of the name. In form of an exclamation, and thus often followed by an exclamation mark.\n#* '''1967''' July 20: [https://www.oireachtas.ie/en/debates/debate/dail/1967-07-20/26/ Questions. Oral Answers. — Free Travel for Old Age Pensioners.] ''Dáil Éireann debates''\n#** [[w:Seán Dunne (politician)|Mr. Dunne]]: \"A small point\", says the Minister for Justice.\n#** [[w:Richie Ryan (politician)|Mr. Ryan]]: Justice, '''how are you'''! He would not recognise it in this world or the next.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|year=2013 December 31|url=https://www.independent.ie/regionals/goreyguardian/news/christmas-how-are-you-well-remember-this-one-for-a-while-29877194.html|title='Christmas '''how are you'''! We'll remember this one for a while'\"|work=Gorey Guardian|passage='Christmas '''how are you'''!' exclaimed Jim O'Hanlon ruefully. 'We will remember this one for quite a while anyway.' He was grateful that at least no one was injured in the incident.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* ''(formal greeting)''\n** {{l|en|how do you do}}?\n* ''(informal greeting)''\n** {{l|en|how are you doing}}?\n** {{l|en|how's it going}}?, [[how's things]]?, [[how's tricks]]?, [[what's up]]? {{qualifier|more informal}}\n** {{l|en|how's it hanging}}? {{qualifier|slang}}\n** See also [[Thesaurus:how are you]]\n* ''(expression of derision)''\n** {{l|en|my foot}}!, {{l|en|my eye}}!, {{l|en|my arse}}!, {{l|en|my ass}}!\n** {{l|en|indeed}}!\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top-see|greeting|how's it going|how}}\n* Abkhaz: {{t|ab|ушԥаҟоу}}, {{t|ab|бышԥаҟоу}}\n* Afrikaans: [[hoe gaan dit]]?\n* Ainu: {{t|ain|[[エイワンケ ア]]?|tr=eiwanke a?}}\n* Akan: {{t|ak|wo ho te sɛn}}\n* Albanian: [[si jeni]]? {{qualifier|formal}}, [[qysh je]]? {{qualifier|informal}}\n*: Arbëresh Albanian: {{t|aae|si rrini|alt=si rrini?}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|aae|si rri|alt=si rri?}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* American Sign Language: {{t|ase|BentB@BackFinger-PalmBack-BentB@CenterChesthigh-PalmBack C@Ulnar-PalmUp-C@CenterChesthigh-PalmUp 1@CenterChesthigh-TipFingerForward}}\n* Amharic: {{t|am|እንደምን አለህ}} {{qualifier|to a male}}, {{t|am|እንደምን አለሽ}} {{qualifier|to a female}}, {{t|am|እንደምን አላችሁ|p}}\n* Apache:\n*: Jicarilla: {{t|apj|haʼáńsį}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|كَيْف الْحال؟}}, {{t+|ar|كَيْفَ حَالُكَ؟}} {{qualifier|to a male, formal}}, {{t+|ar|كَيْف حَالَك؟}} {{qualifier|to a male, informal}}; {{t+|ar|كَيْفَ حَالُكِ؟}} {{qualifier|to a female, formal}}, {{t+|ar|كَيْف حَالِك؟}} {{qualifier|to a female, informal}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|ازيك|alt=إِزَّيَّك؟|m|tr=izzáyyak?}} {{qualifier|to a male}}; {{t|arz|ازيك|alt=إِزَّيِّك؟|f|tr=izzáyyik?}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|كيفك|alt=كيفَك؟|m|tr=kēfak?}} {{qualifier|to a male}}; {{t|acw|كيفك|alt=كيفِك؟|f|tr=kēfik?}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: Mesopotamian Arabic: {{t|apc|شْلُونَك؟|tr=šlōnak?|m}} {{qualifier|to a male}}; {{t|apc|شْلُونَك؟|tr=šlōnik?|f}}, {{t|apc|شْلُونَك؟|tr=šlōnič?|f}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|لا باس؟|tr=lā bās?}}, {{t|ary|كي داير|tr=kī dāyer}} {{qualifier|to a male}}, {{t|ary|كي دايرة|tr=kī dāyra}} {{qualifier|to a female}}, {{t|ary|كيف عامل|tr=kīf ʕāmel}} {{qualifier|to a male}}, {{t|ary|كيف عاملة|tr=kīf ʕāmla}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n*: North Levantine Arabic: {{t|apc|كِيفَك؟|m|tr=kīfak?}} {{qualifier|to a male}}; {{t|apc|كِيفِك؟|m|tr=kīfik?}} {{qualifier|to a female}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܘܬ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܘܸܬ؟}} {{qualifier|to a male}}, {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܘܬܝ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܘܵܬܝ؟}} {{qualifier|to a female}}, {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܬܘܢ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܬܘܿܢ؟}} {{qualifier|to a group}}, {{t|aii|ܕܐܟܝ ܝܠܗ ܟܝܦܘܟ|alt=ܕܵܐܟ݂ܝܼ ܝܠܹܗ ܟܲܝܦܘܼܟ݂؟}} {{qualifier|more formal; to a male}}, {{t|aii|ܐܝܟܢܐ ܟܐ ܚܙܝܬ ܢܦܫܘܟ|alt=ܐܲܝܟܲܢܵܐ ܟܹܐ ܚܵܙܹܝܬ ܢܲܦ̮ܫܘܼܟ݂؟}} {{qualifier|more formal; to a male}}\n*: Classical Syriac:\n* Arapaho: [[kooni'ííni]]?\n* Armenian: {{t|hy|ինչպե՞ս ես}} {{qualifier|singular}}, {{t|hy|ո՞նց ես}} {{qualifier|singular}}, {{t|hy|ինչպե՞ս եք}} {{qualifier|polite or plural}}, {{t|hy|ո՞նց եք}} {{qualifier|polite or plural}}\n* Assamese: {{t|as|আপোনাৰ ভালনে?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|as|তোমাৰ ভালনে?}} {{q|familiar}}, {{t|as|তোৰ ভালনে?}} {{q|informal}}, {{t|as|আপুনি ভালে আছেনে?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|as|তুমি ভালে আছানে?}} {{q|familiar}}, {{t|as|তই ভালে আছনে?}} {{q|informal}}, {{t|as|কি খবৰ?}} {{q|familiar, informal}}, {{t|as|আপুনি কেনে আছে?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|as|তুমি কেনে আছা?}} {{q|familiar}}, {{t|as|তই কেনে আছ?}} {{q|informal}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|cómo tas}}, {{t|ast|qué faes}}\n* Atayal: {{t|tay|lokah su ga}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|necəsən|c}} {{qualifier|(informal)}}\n* Bashkir: {{t|ba|хәлдәр нисек?}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|zer moduz}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|як спра́вы?}}, {{t|be|як пажыва́еш?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|be|як пажыва́еце?}} {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|আপনি কেমন আছেন?}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|bn|তুমি কেমন আছ?}} {{qualifier|familiar}}, {{t+|bn|তুই কেমন আছিস?}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{t|bcl|kumusta na?}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|как си}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|bg|как сте}}? {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* Burmese: {{t|my|နေကောင်းရဲ့လား။}}, {{t|my|နေကောင်းလား။}}\n* Catalan: {{t|ca|com estàs}}?, {{qualifier|formal}} {{t|ca|com està}}?, {{qualifier|informal}} {{t|ca|com va}}?\n* Cebuano: {{t|ceb|kumusta}}?, {{t|ceb|kumusta na ka}}?\n* Chamorro: {{t|ch|kao mamaolek ha' hao}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|ch|håfa tatatmanu hao}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Chechen: {{t|ce|муха ду гӏуллакхаш?}}\n* Cherokee: {{t|chr|ᏙᎯᏧ?}}\n* Chichewa: {{t|ny|muli bwanji?}}\n* Chickasaw: {{t|cic|hallito chokma chinchokma}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t+|yue|你好嗎|alt=你好嗎？|tr=nei5 hou2 maa3?}}\n*: Dungan: {{t|dng|задини?}}, {{t|dng|задигә?}}, {{t|dng|ни хо ма?}}, {{t|dng|ни җўди хома?}}\n*: Hakka: {{t|hak|你好冇|tr=ngì-hó-mò / nì-hó-mò / ǹ-hó-mò / ǹg-hó-mò}}\n*: Hokkien: {{t|nan-hbl|[[汝]][[好勢]][[無]]？|tr=lí hó-sè--bô? / lír hó-sè--bô? / lú hó-sè--bô?}}, {{t|nan-hbl|你好無|alt=汝好無？|tr=lí hó--bô? / lír hó--bô? / lú hó--bô?}}, {{t|nan-hbl|[[汝]][[較]][[好]][[無]]？|tr=lí khà hó--bô? / lír khà hó--bô? / lú khà hó--bô?}}, {{t|nan-hbl|[[汝]][[食]][[未]]？|tr=lí chia̍h bē? / lír chia̍h bēr? / lí chia̍h bōe? / lú chia̍h bōe? / lír chia̍h běr?}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|你好嗎|alt=你好嗎？|tr=nǐhǎo ma?}} (''informal singular'')\n*: Wu: {{t|wuu|儂好𠲎？|tr=6non 5hau 0va}}\n* Chinook Jargon: {{t|chn|qʰata mayka}}\n* Choctaw: {{t|cho|chim achukma̱?}}\n* Circassian:\n*: West Circassian: {{t|ady|дауэ ущыт?}}\n* Comorian:\n*: Ngazidja Comorian: {{t|zdj|haɓari ?}}, {{t|zdj|hufanyiha dje ?}}, {{t|zdj|ngawe dje ?}}, {{t|zdj|hukaantsi dje?}}\n* Cornish: {{t|kw|fatla genes}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{t|crh|nasılsıñız?}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|jak se máš}}? (''informal singular''), {{t+|cs|jak se máte}}? {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* Dakota: {{t|dak|token yauŋ he?}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|hvordan har du det?}}, {{t+|da|hvordan går det?}}\n* Deori: {{t|der|dakiya chuina?}} {{q|formal}}, {{t|der|noi chuina?}} {{q|familiar}}\n* Dusun:\n*: Central Dusun: {{t|dtp|nunu kabar?}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|hoe gaat het}}?, {{t|nl|hoe is het}}?, {{qualifier|informal}} {{t|nl|alles goed}}?\n* Esperanto: [[kiel vi fartas]]?\n* Estonian: {{t|et|kuidas läheb}}?, {{t|et|kuidas käsi käib?}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|hvussu gongur}}?\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kuinka voitte}}? {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t+|fi|kuinka voit}}? {{qualifier|less formal}}, {{t+|fi|miten menee}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t+|fi|mitä kuuluu|alt=mitä kuuluu?}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|comment allez-vous|alt=comment allez-vous ?}} (''formal or plural''), {{t+|fr|comment vas-tu|alt=comment vas-tu ?}} (''informal singular''), {{t+|fr|ça va|alt=ça va ?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t+|fr|comment ça va|alt=comment ça va ?}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{t|fy|hoe giet it?}}, {{t|fy|hoe is it mei dy?}}, {{t|fy|hoe is it mei jo?}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|como vai?}}, {{t|gl|como estás}}?\n* Garo: {{t|grt|namengama?}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|როგორა ხარ?}} {{qualifier|informal singular}}, {{t|ka|როგორ ბრძანდებით?}} {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* German: {{t+|de|wie geht es dir}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|de|wie geht es Ihnen}}? {{qualifier|formal singular/plural}}, {{t|de|wie geht es}}? / {{t+|de|wie geht's|alt=wie geht’s?}}, {{t|de|wie geht es euch}}? {{qualifier|informal plural}}\n*: Alemannic German: {{t|gsw|wie gaat s dir?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|gsw|wie gaat s Ine?}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Greek: {{qualifier|informal, singular}} {{t+|el|τι κάνεις|alt=τι κάνεις;}}, {{qualifier|formal, plural}} {{t|el|τι κάνετε|alt=τι κάνετε;}}, {{qualifier|informal, singular}} {{t|el|πώς είσαι;}}, {{qualifier|formal, plural}} {{t|el|πώς είστε;}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|τί πράσσεις}}, {{t|grc|πῶς ἔχεις}}\n* Gujarati: {{t|gu|તમે કેમ છો}}? {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|gu|કેમ છે}}? {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Haitian Creole: {{t-needed|ht}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|pehea ʻoe}}?\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|מה שלומך|alt=?מה שלומך|tr=ma shlomkha?}} (''singular male''), (ma shlomekh?) (''singular female''), (ma shlomkhem?) (''plural male''), (ma shlomkhen?) (''plural female'')\n* Hiligaynon: {{t|hil|kamusta}}?, kamusta ka?\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|क्या हाल है|alt=क्या हाल है?}}, {{t|hi|आप कैसे हैं|alt=आप कैसे हैं?}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|hi|कैसे हो|alt=कैसे हो?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|hi|कैसा चल रहा है|alt=कैसा चल रहा है?}}\n* Hmong:\n*: Green Hmong: {{t|hnj|koj nyob le caag lawm}}?\n*: Northern Qiandong Miao: {{t|hea|Mongx vut hol}}?\n*: Southern Qiandong Miao: {{t|hms|Moux chud jib nangd}}?\n*: White Hmong: {{t|mww|koj puas nyob zoo}}?\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|hogy vagy|alt=hogy vagy?}} {{q|informal}}, {{t+|hu|hogy van|alt=hogy van?}} {{q|formal}}\n* Hunsrik: {{t|hrx|alles gut}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|hvað segirðu gott}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t+|is|hvað segir þú gott}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|is|hvað segiði gott}}? (''informal and plural''), {{t|is|hvað segið þið gott}}? (''informal and plural''), {{t|is|hvað segið þér gott}}? (''formal, singular and plural''), {{t|is|hvað segirðu}}? (''singular and informal''), {{t+|is|hvað segir þú}}? (''singular and informal''), {{t|is|hvernig hefurðu það?}}, {{t|is|hvað syngur í þér?}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|quale vu standas}}?\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|apa kabar}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|[[mitä kuuluu]]?}}\n* Irish: {{qualifier|singular, Munster}} {{t|ga|conas tá tú|alt=conas tá tú?}}, {{t|ga|conas taoi|alt=conas taoi?}}, {{t|ga|conas tánn tú|alt=conas tánn tú?}}, {{qualifier|plural, Munster}} {{t|ga|conas tá sibh|alt=conas tá sibh?}}, {{t|ga|conas tánn sibh|alt=conas tánn sibh?}}, {{qualifier|singular, Connacht}} {{t|ga|cén chaoi a bhfuil tú|alt=cén chaoi a bhfuil tú?}}, {{qualifier|plural, Connacht}} {{t|ga|cén chaoi a bhfuil sibh|alt=cén chaoi a bhfuil sibh?}}, {{qualifier|singular, Ulster}} {{t|ga|cad é an dóigh atá ort|alt=cad é an dóigh atá ort?}}, {{t|ga|cad é mar tá tú|alt=cad é mar tá tú?}}, {{qualifier|plural, Ulster}} {{t|ga|cad é mar tá sibh|alt=cad é mar tá sibh?}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|come stai?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|it|come sta?}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Iu Mien: {{t|ium|yiem longx nyei saah?}}, {{t|ium|yiem longx nyei fai?}}\n* Ivatan: {{t|ivv|ara ca mangu?}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|お元気ですか|tr=おげんきですか, o-genki desu ka}} {{qualifier|polite}}, {{t|ja|ご機嫌いかがですか|tr=ごきげんいかがですか, go-kigen ikaga desu ka}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Jeju: {{t|jje|펜안ᄒᆞᆸ데강?}} {{qualifier|polite}}, {{t|jje|펜안헨?}} {{qualifier|casual}}, {{t|jje|펜안헷인야?}} {{qualifier|casual}}, {{t|jje|어떵 살아져ᇝ우과?}} {{qualifier|polite}}, {{t|jje|어떵 살아ᇝ어?}} {{qualifier|casual}}\n* Jingpho: [[hkam kaja ai i]]?\n* Kannada: {{t|kn|ನೀವು ಹೇಗಿದ್ದೀರ?}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|komusta}}, {{t|pam|komusta naka?}}, {{t|pam|komusta nakayo?}}, {{t|pam|mipakananu naka?}}, {{t|pam|mipakananu nakayo?}},\n* Karachay-Balkar: {{t|krc|къалайса|alt=къалайса?}}\n* Kazakh: {{t+|kk|қалайсың?}}\n* Khmer: {{t|km|សុខសប្បាយជាទេ?}}\n* Kikuyu: {{t|ki|wĩ mwega?}}\n* Konkani: {{t|kok|कशें आसति तुम्हि?|tr=kaśẽ āsati tumhi}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|처음 뵙겠습니다}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|ko|어떻게 지내세요?}}, {{t|ko|잘 지냈어요?}}, {{t+|ko|안녕-하세요?}} {{qualifier|polite}}, {{t|ko|안녕-하십니까?}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t+|ko|안녕?}} {{qualifier|casual}}\n* Kumyk: {{t|kum|ишлер нечикдир}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|چۆنی}}, {{t|ckb|چۆنی باشی}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|кандайсыз?}}\n* Ladin: {{t|lld|co vala pa?}}\n* Lakota: {{t|lkt|toníkhetu he?}}, {{t|lkt|toúŋkhetupi he?|p}}\n* Lao: {{t|lo|ສະບາຍດີບໍ່}}?\n* Latgalian: [[kai vadās]]?, [[kai tev vadās]]? {{qualifier|informal}}, [[kai jums vadās]]? {{qualifier|formal}}, [[kai dzeivoj]]? {{qualifier|informal}}, [[kai dzeivojat]]? {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Latin: [[quid agis]]?, [[quomodo]] [[es]]?\n* Latvian: [[kā iet]]?, [[kā tev iet]]? {{qualifier|informal}}, [[kā klājas]]?, [[kā jums klājas]]? {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Lithuanian: [[kaip tau sekasi]]?\n* Louisiana Creole: {{t|lou|komen to yê|alt=komen to yê?}}, {{t|lou|komen ça va|alt=komen ça va?}}, {{t|lou|komen lê zafær|alt=komen lê zafær?}}\n* Lower Tanana: {{t|taa|do'it'a}}\n* Low German:\n*: German Low German: {{t|nds-de|woans geiht di dat?}}, {{t|nds-de|woans geiht?}}\n* Ludian: {{t|lud|kutt elät?}}\n* Luo: {{t|luo|ithi nadi}} {{qualifier|to one person}}, {{t|luo|uthi nadi}} {{qualifier|to multiple people}}\n* Macanese: {{t|mzs|como tá vai?}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|ка́ко си?}} (''informal or singular''), {{t|mk|ка́ко сте?}} (''formal or plural''), {{t|mk|што правиш}}, {{t|mk|што правите}}\n* Malay: {{t+|ms|apa khabar}}\n* Malayalam: {{t|ml|എങ്ങനെയിരിക്കുന്നു?}}\n* Maltese: [[kif int]]? {{g|s}}, [[kif intkom]]? {{g|p}}\n* Mandingo:\n*: Mandinka: {{t|mnk|i be nyaadi}}\n* Manx: {{qualifier|singular informal}} {{t|gv|kys t'ou}}, {{qualifier|plural or formal singular}} {{t|gv|kys ta shiu}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|kei te pēhea koe?}}\n* Mapudungun: {{t|arn|kümelkaleymi}}\n* Miskito: [[nahkisma]]?\n* Miwok:\n*: Central Sierra Miwok: {{t|csm|miṭip·kur}}\n* Mòcheno: {{t|mhn|bia geat s?}}\n* Mohawk: {{t|moh|oh niiohtonhátie?}},  {{t|moh|skennen’kó:wa ken?}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|сайн байна уу?}}, {{t|mn|сонин сайхан юу байна вэ?}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|ąąʼ haʼíí baa naniná?}}\n* Nootka: {{t|nuk|wiikšahik}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|coume tchi que l'affaire va?}} {{qualifier|Guernsey}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|hvordan står det til?}}, {{t|nb|hvordan går det?}}, {{t|nb|hvordan har du det?}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|korleis går det?}}, {{t|nn|korleis har du det?}}, {{t|nn|korleis står det til?}}\n* Occitan: [[va plan]]&nbsp;?\n* Ojibwe: {{t|oj|aaniin ezhi-ayaayan?}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|hū færest þū?}}, {{t|ang|hu eart þu|alt=hū eart þū?}}\n* Old Tupi: {{t|tpw|ereîkobépe}}\n* Palauan: [[ke ua ngerang]]?\n* Pashto: {{t|ps|څنگه يې؟}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{qualifier|familiar and colloquial}} {{t|fa-ira|حالِت چِطورِه؟|tr=hâlet četor-e?}}, {{t|fa-ira|چِطوری؟|tr=četori?}}; {{qualifier|polite and colloquial}} {{t|fa-ira|حالِ شُما چِطورِه؟|tr=hâl-e šomâ četor-e?}}, {{t|fa-ira|حالِتان چِطورِه؟|tr=hâletân četor-e?}}; {{qualifier|polite and formal}} {{t|fa-ira|حالِ شُما چِطور اَسْت؟|tr=hâl-e šomâ četor ast?}}, {{t|fa-ira|حالِتان چِطور اَسْت؟|tr=hâletân četor ast?}}, {{t|fa-ira|حالِت خوبِه؟|tr=hâlet xube?}}\n* Pitcairn-Norfolk: {{t|pih|whutta-waye?}}\n* Polish: [[jak się masz]]? {{qualifier|singular}}, [[jak się macie]]? {{qualifier|plural}}; [[co słychać]]?; {{t|pl|co u ciebie?}} {{qualifier|singular}}, {{t|pl|co u was?}} {{qualifier|plural}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|como vai}}? {{t|pt|como está}}? {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|pt|como estás}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|pt|como você vai?}}, {{t+|pt|tudo bem?}}\n* Quechua: {{t|qu|imainallam kackanki?}}\n* Rapa Nui: {{t|rap|pehe koe?}}\n* Romani: {{t|rom|sar san}} {{qualifier|to one person}}, {{t|rom|sar sen}} {{qualifier|to more than one person}}, {{t|rom|so maj keres}} {{qualifier|to one person}}, {{t|rom|so maj keren}} {{qualifier|to more than one person}}\n* Romanian: [[ce mai faceți]]? {{qualifier|formal}}, [[ce mai faci]]? {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|как дела́?}}, {{t|ru|как пожива́ешь?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|ru|как пожива́ете?}} {{qualifier|formal or plural}}\n* Saanich: {{t|str|ÁȽE¸ E SW̱ U¸ Í¸ OL¸}}\n* Sami:\n*: Northern Sami: {{t|se|mii gullo?}}, {{t|se|mo manná?}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n*: Southern Sami: {{t|sma|guktie veasoeh}}\n* Samoan: {{t|sm|ʻo ā mai ʻoe}}?\n* Santali: {{t|sat|ᱚᱠᱟ ᱞᱮᱠᱟ ᱢᱮᱱᱟᱢᱟ?}}\n* Scots: {{t|sco|hoo are ye}}?, {{t|sco|whit like}}?\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|ciamar a tha thu}}? (''informal singular''), {{t|gd|ciamar a tha sibh}}? (''plural or formal singular''), {{qualifier|singular, Argyll}} {{t|gd|dè mar a tha thu?}}, {{qualifier|plural, Argyll}} {{t|gd|dè mar a tha sibh?}}\n* Semai: {{t|sea|ma igah}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|како си?}} (''informal singular''), {{t|sh|како сте?}} (''formal or plural'')\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|kako si?}} (''informal singular''), {{t|sh|kako ste?}} (''formal or plural'')\n* Sinhalese: {{t|si|කොහොමද සැප සනිප}}\n* Slovak: [[ako sa máš]]? (informal or singular), [[ako sa máte]]? (formal or plural)\n* Slovene: [[kako si]]? (''informal or singular''), [[kako ste]]? (''formal or plural'')\n* Spanish: {{t|es|[[¿cómo]] + ''present indicative'' [[estar]] (+ ''subject pronoun'')?}}, {{t|es|¿qué tal?}} {{q|informal}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|fa a waka}}?, {{t|srn|fa a e go}}?, {{t|srn|fa yu tan}}?, {{t|srn|fa fu yu}}?, {{t|srn|fa yu de}}?, {{t|srn|ofa}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|srn|fa}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Svan: {{t|sva|მაგვართ ხარი?}}, {{t|sva|იმჟი ხარი?}}\n* Swahili: [[habari gani]]?, {{t+|sw|hujambo}}\n* Swedish: {{t|sv|hur är det}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|sv|hur är läget}}? {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|sv|hur står det till}}?, {{t|sv|hur mår du?}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|kumusta}}?, {{t|tl|kumusta ka}}?, {{t|tl|kumusta ka na}}?, {{t|tl|kumusta na}}?\n* Tamil: {{t|ta|எப்படி இருக்கீங்க}}, {{t|ta|சௌக்கியமா?|lit=are you well?}}\n* Tarifit: {{t|rif|mamc tedjid?}}\n* Tashelhit: {{t|shi|mamnk ad tgit?}}, {{t|shi|manzakin}} {{qualifier|to a male}},  {{t|shi|manzakmmin}} {{q|to a female}}\n* Telugu: {{t|te|ఎలా ఉన్నారు}}\n* Tetum: {{t-needed|tet}}\n* Tetun Dili: {{t-needed|tdt}}\n* Thai: {{t|th|สบายดีไหม}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{t|tpi|yu orait}}\n* Tongan: {{t|to|fēfē hake?}}\n* Tswana: {{t|tn|o tsogile jang}}\n* Turkish: [[nasılsınız]]? {{qualifier|formal}}, [[nasılsın]]? {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Turkmen: {{t|tk|gurgunmyň}}\n* Udi: {{t|udi|гьетаьрну? |s|tr=hetærnu|lit=how-you(2SG)?}}, {{t|udi|гьетаьрнан?|p|tr=hetærnan|lit=How-you(2PL)?}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|як спра́ви?}}, {{t|uk|як ся ма́єш?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|uk|як ся ма́єте?}} {{qualifier|informal plural}}, {{t|uk|як пожива́єш?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|uk|як пожива́єте?}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|uk|як діла́?}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|kulamàlsi hàch?}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|کْیا حال ہَے؟}}, {{t|ur|آپ کَیسے ہَیں؟}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|ur|کَیسے ہو؟}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Uyghur: {{t-needed|ug}}\n* Uzbek: {{t|uz|qalaysan?}}, {{t|uz|qalaysiz?}}\n* Veps: {{t|vep|kut elät?}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|khoẻ không?}}, {{t|vi|khoẻ chứ?}}, {{t|vi|dạo này sao?}}, {{t|vi|ăn cơm chưa?}}, {{t|vi|ăn cơm chửa?}} {{qualifier|Thanh Hóa}}\n* Volapük: {{t|vo|lio stadol-li?}}\n* Võro: {{t|vro|kuis lätt?}}\n* Votic: {{t|vot|kui meneb?}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|ké novele|alt=ké novele?}}, {{t+|wa|ké novele a Lidje|alt=ké novele a Lidje?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t+|wa|ça vos va|alt=ça vos va?}}, {{t+|wa|ça_t’_va}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|sut wyt ti|alt=sut wyt ti?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|cy|sut dach chi|alt=sut dach chi?}} {{qualifier|formal}}\n* Winnebago: {{t|win|jaanįsge raje?}}\n* Xhosa: {{t|xh|unjani?}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|וואָס הערט זיך בײַ דיר?}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{t|yi|וואָס מאַכסטו?}} {{qualifier|familiar}}, {{t|yi|וואָס מאַכט איר?}} {{qualifier|formal}}, {{t|yi|וואָס מאַכט אַ ייִד?}} {{qualifier|casual, to another Jew}}, {{t|yi|וואָס טוט זיך?}} {{qualifier|casual}}, {{t|yi|וואָס הערט זיך?}}\n* Yoruba: {{t|yo|ṣé àlàáfíà l'ẹ wà}}? {{qualifier|polite}}, {{t|yo|ṣé àlàáfíà ni}}?, {{t|yo|ṣé dáadáa ni}}?, {{t|yo|báwo ni}}? {{qualifier|casual}}\n* Yucatec Maya: {{t|yua|¿bix a beel?}}\n* Yup'ik: {{t|esu|qaillun ayuqsit?}}, {{t|esu|cangacit?}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|senin ê?}}, {{t|zza|hal kêf}}\n* Zulu: {{t+|zu|unjani?}} {{qualifier|singular}}, {{t|zu|ninjani?}} {{qualifier|plural}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aehooruwy|who are you}}\n\n{{cln|en|questions|sentences|greetings}}"}}